{"title_page": "Tosa Maidan", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Tosa Maidan\n| other_name              = \n| nickname                = \n| settlement_type         = Meadow\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| pushpin_map             = India Jammu and Kashmir#India\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Jammu and Kashmir ('' Kashmir''')\n| coordinates             = {{coord|33|55|4|N|74|29|57|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = [[India]]\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Jammu and Kashmir]]\n| subdivision_type2       = Khag\n\n| subdivision_name2       =\n| established_title       = \n| established_date        =\n| founder                 = \n| named_for               = \n| government_type         =\n| governing_body          = <!-- Established -->\n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          = \n| area_rank               = \n| area_total_km2          = \n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = \n| population_total        = \n| population_as_of        = \n| population_rank         = \n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      = \n| population_footnotes    = \n| demographics_type1      = Languages\n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Kashmiri people|Kashmiri]]\n|demographics1_title2    = Local\n| demographics1_info2     = [[Kashmiri language|Kashmiri]]\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        =  [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code             = 193411\n| registration_plate      = \n| website                 = \n| footnotes               = \n}}\n\n'''Tosa Maidan''' (or '''Toshamaidan''') is a [[meadow]] in Khag tehsil of  [[Budgam]] district of [[Jammu and Kashmir]], [[India]]. The name also marks the historic '''Tosa Maidan route''' into the Kashmir Valley from the [[Poonch River|Poonch Valley]]. In fact, the original name of Tosa Maidan appears to have been \"Tosa Marg\".<ref>{{citation |editor-last=Begley |editor-first=Wayne Edison |title=The Shah Jahan nama of 'Inayat Khan: An abridged history of the Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan, compiled by his royal librarian |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=n_BtAAAAMAAJ |year=1990 |publisher=Oxford University Press |pp=127\u2013128}}: \"In that vale resembling Paradise, there are besides several summer retreats such as no other region can boast of. One is called the Godi Marg, another the Tosa Marg; and the profusion of flowers and plants in both those places is so great that you can pluck at least 100 different kinds of blossoms off a single parterre.\"</ref> [[Mahmud of Ghazni]] and the Sikh monarch [[Ranjit Singh]] attempted to invade the Kashmir Valley via this route.\n\n== The Meadow ==\nTosa Maidan is a valley full of meadows surrounded by Pir Panchal ranges. 3 miles in length and 1.5 miles in breadth, it is 53 km distant from Srinagar. it is known as the king of meadows. Tosa Maidan is in khag tehsil of Budgam district of Jammu and Kashmir. Tosa Maidan is not only famous as a pasture but also for its historical background. Bounded by dense forests, it is situated about 10 kms from Khag in the mountains of the Himalayan range. After crossing the upper mountain reaches of Drang, Zakhora and other small villages, one reaches the pasture of Tosa Maidan. It is said that Tosa Maidan is one of those pastures which the shepherds of other neighbouring countries also used to visit in ancient times. The Mughals used to go to Poonch using this route. It is said that they had constructed a seven-storeyed building \u2013 Dam-Dam \u2013 here. \n\nTosa Maidan is the largest pasture in its surrounding areas, 3 miles in length and 1.5 miles in width. Sky-touching [[Cedrus deodara|deodars]] fence this pasture presenting a view of a green carpet in summer. During the summer, the camps of the Gujjar community and shepherds with their grazing sheep in the pastures present a riveting picture. Also, the fragrance of wild flowers refreshes the whole environment.\n\n== The route ==\n{{OSM Location map\n| coord = {{coord|33.86|74.41}}   <!-- Map center -->\n| float = right\n| zoom = 10\n| width = 350 \n| height = 250\n| caption = <center>Tosa Maidan route</center>\n| nolabels = 1\n<!-- minimap -->\n| minimap = file\n| mini-file = India Jammu and Kashmir location map.svg\n| mini-width = 100\n| mini-height = 73\n| minipog-x = 23\n| minipog-y = 44\n| scalemark = 120\n| shape = image\n<!-- Tosa Maidan -->\n| mark-coord1 = {{coord|33|55|4|N|74|29|57|E}}\n| mark1 = Green pog.svg\n| mark-size1 = 10\n| label1 = Tosa Maidan\n| label-size1 = 10 \n| label-color1 = hard green\n| label-pos1 = top | label-offset-x1 = 0 | label-offset-y1 = 0\n| mark-title1 = Tosa Maidan\n| mark-image1 =\n| mark-description1 = meadow\n<!-- Danam Sar -->\n| mark-coord2 = {{coord|33.866|74.416}} \n| mark2 = Blue pog.svg \n| mark-size2 = 8\n| label2 = Danam Sar\n| label-size2 = 10 \n| label-color2 = hard blue\n| label-pos2 = right |label-offset-x2 = 0 |label-offset-y2 = 0\n| mark-title2 = Danam Sar\n| mark-image2 =\n| mark-description2 = lake\n<!-- Chinamarg Gali -->\n| mark-coord3 = {{coord|33.8803|74.4045}} \n| mark3 = Mountain pass 12x12 e.svg\n| mark-size3 = 12\n| label3 = Chinamarg Gali\n| label-size3 = 10 \n| label-color3 = hard red\n| label-pos3 = top |label-offset-x3 = 0 |label-offset-y3 = 0\n| mark-title3 = Chinamarg Gali\n| mark-image3 =\n| mark-description3 = Mountain pass for descent to Loran valley\n<!-- Pam Sar  -->\n| mark-coord4 = {{coord|33.8208|74.4509}} \n| mark4 = Blue pog.svg\n| mark-size4 = 8\n| label4 = Pam Sar\n| label-size4 = 10 \n| label-color4 = hard blue\n| label-