ard Harris\n| Peter Luke (P)\nJames Ferman (D)\n| \n|-\n| 16 February 1966\n| A Game - Like - Only a Game\n| John Hopkins\n| Peter Luke (P)\nChristopher Morahan (D)\n| \n|-\n| 23 February 1966\n| Why Aren't You Famous?\n| Ernie Gebler\n| Peter Luke (P)\nPeter Sasdy (D)\n| \n|-\n| 2 March 1966\n| Macready's Gala\n| Hugh Whitemore\n| Peter Luke (P)\nWaris Hussein (D)\n| \n|-\n| 9 March 1966\n| A Walk in the Sea\n| James Hanley\n| Peter Luke (P)\nGeoffrey Nethercott (D)\n| \n|-\n| 16 March 1966\n| Boy in the Smoke\n| Patrick Galvin\n| Peter Luke (P)\nWilliam Slater (D)\n| First shown in the series Londoners on BBC2 13/05/1965.\n|-\n| 23 March 1966\n| Barlowe of the Car Park\n| Paul Ableman\n| Peter Luke (P)\nGareth Davies (D)\n| \n|-\n| 30 March 1966\n| The Portsmouth Defence\n| Nemone Lethbridge\n| Peter Luke (P)\nJames MacTaggart (D)\n| \n|-\n| 6 April 1966\n| [[Pity_About_the_Abbey|Pity about the Abbey]]\n| John Betjeman and Stewart Farrar\n| Peter Luke (P)\nIan Curteis (D)\n| First shown in the series Londoners on BBC2 29/07/1965.\n|-\n| 13 April 1966\n| The Big Man Coughed and Died\n| Brian Wright\n| Peter Luke (P)\nPeter Duguid (D)\n| \n|-\n| 20 April 1966\n| The Snow Ball\n| Brigid Brophy\nDramatised by Ursula Gray.\n| Peter Luke (P)\nCharles Jarrott (D)\n| \n|-\n| 27 April 1966\n| A Cheery Soul\n| Patrick White\nAdapted by Jonquil Antony\n| Peter Luke (P)\nGilchrist Calder (D)\n| \n|-\n| 4 May 1966\n| The Connoisseur\n| Hugo Charteris\n| Peter Luke (P)\nWaris Hussein (D)\n| \n|-\n| 11 May 1966\n| The Retreat\n| Hugh Leonard\n| Peter Luke (P)\nCharles Jarrott (D)\n| \n|-\n| 18 May 1966\n| Ape and Essence\n| Aldous Huxley.\nDramatised by John Finch.\n| Peter Luke (P)\nDavid Benedictus (D)\n| \n|-\n| 25 May 1966\n| Toddler on the Run\n| From the novel by Shena MacKay.\n| Peter Luke (P)\nJames MacTaggart (D)\n| \n|-\n| 1 June 1966\n| The Executioner\n| Robert Muller\n| Peter Luke (P)\nMichael Hayes (D)\n| \n|-\n| 8 June 1966\n| Way Off Beat\n| David Turner\n| James